EEVEE = Blenders Default Render Engine = Fast but not accurate, essentially a game engine 'Real Time'(bad for realism) Vs 'RayTrace/PathTrace/Offline Engine' = Accurate, but slow
Tut - 'Render' -> Change from 'EEVEE' to 'Cycles' - Computer will work very hard, you can hear it, the image goes grainy and gets slowly clearer as you stand still - 
  Change from CPU to GPU = 'Edit' -> 'Preferences' -> 'System'
'Cuda' = NVIDIA - Cards 1080 and less / 'Optix' = ~2000 series / 'HIP' = AMD / 'oneAPI' = Apple
'Denoiser' = used to remove the 'noise'(grainy effect) = Esnure this is enabled in the 'Properties' -> 'Render'
Lighting - 
'Alt + G' = Will cause an object to appear in the center
'SubSurface Scattering' = for 'Fleshy Objects' - light will show through fingers - It's not a hard object - Like Metallic = Weight is either a 0 or 1 - Couldn't find it in the tutorial, looked for a while, it's not there
  'radius' = When using this(if you can find it) it's set up for skin by default, so you need to reduce the radius(x,y,z/r,g,b) to '1' or else it will change the color of your object
  'scale' = the thickness of the object, in meters
  -Makes the shadows look better, allows some light to pass through, makes the icing/donut look softer and more like food
https://docs.blender.org/manual/en/latest/render/shader_nodes/shader/sss.html

